Alice Davenport https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alice_Davenport 0 Alice Davenport (February 29, 1864 – June 24, 1936) was an American film actress. She appeared in 140 films between 1911 and 1930. She was born Alice Shepphard in New York, New York, and died in Los Angeles, California. She made her stage debut at age five. Davenport married silent actor, director, and talkie character actor Harry Davenport. Actress Dorothy Davenport was their daughter.
